Americans believe that all citizens have equal access to our fundamental democratic right: voting. But the fact is racial politics still suppress votes.

name: axios
text:
Laws restricting voting are less overt than in the days of segregation. But many impediments ‚Äî some subtle, some blatant ‚Äî remain for Americans of color, writes @sarakgoo and @margarettalev. That's changing at this very moment ‚Äî slowly, and very unevenly.
